<span id="freeTextContainer1581307703316499557">I wanted to love this book...people I trust tout it as their favorite, but I just didn&apos;t. Perhaps it&apos;s the disjointed nature of the stories, but I just couldn&apos;t get involved with any of the characters. The writing has some beautiful little gems along the way--exquisite when you find them--but I&apos;m not sure I found them worth the digging. Perhaps if I&apos;d &quot;gotten it&quot; earlier that this was not a single story, but a series of barely connected stories, I might have enjoyed it more. I kept trying to tie</span>
  <span id="freeText1581307703316499557" style="display:none">I wanted to love this book...people I trust tout it as their favorite, but I just didn't. Perhaps it's the disjointed nature of the stories, but I just couldn't get involved with any of the characters. The writing has some beautiful little gems along the way--exquisite when you find them--but I'm not sure I found them worth the digging. Perhaps if I'd "gotten it" earlier that this was not a single story, but a series of barely connected stories, I might have enjoyed it more. I kept trying to tie things together and follow the threads that never fully connect. </span>
