        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1138394655" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8603528193658955609">What is the fuss about? I read this for my book group and am feeling pretty neutral about it. Yes, it is well-written. In fact the beauty of the language was the only thing that kept me going (that and the length -at 214 pages, it&apos;s a pretty quick read!) And I suppose if I were considering leading the life of an ex pat in Mexico, I might find it of interest. But the stories of the townspeople that intersperse the book were spare, and left more questions than they answered. And I never felt that </span>
  <span id="freeText8603528193658955609" style="display:none">What is the fuss about? I read this for my book group and am feeling pretty neutral about it. Yes, it is well-written. In fact the beauty of the language was the only thing that kept me going (that and the length -at 214 pages, it's a pretty quick read!) And I suppose if I were considering leading the life of an ex pat in Mexico, I might find it of interest. But the stories of the townspeople that intersperse the book were spare, and left more questions than they answered. And I never felt that I knew the main characters, Richard and Sara, all that well. The impulse that took them to Ibarra in the first place? Maybe I can understand that. But so much of their daily lives, their relationship, their relationships with the folks they left behind, went unsaid. But then, maybe I'm just missing something here? I'll let my book group help me sort it out! </span>
  <a data-text-id="8603528193658955609" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


